<task id="043" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4">
  <metadata>
    <title>W-5 (FR-03): Wire Context → Workspace mount source for one wizard (recommended: Create Project) — wizard completion dispatches widget_load mounting result as workspace tab</title>
    <phase>4: Workspace builder + mount-source wiring</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>6</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>010</dependencies>
    <blocks>none</blocks>
    <tags>frontend, react, fluent-ui, e2e-test, deploy</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies `.ts/.tsx` source; tags include `frontend`/`react`/`fluent-ui`; 10+ steps; depends on 010 (W-1 model); applies multiple load-bearing ADRs (021, 022, 025, 028). FULL rigor — Step 9.5 quality gates mandatory.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>E</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Wire ONE Context-pane wizard (recommended: Create Project) to add an "Add result to
    Workspace" final step. On completion of that final step, dispatch `widget_load` on the
    `PaneEventBus.workspace` channel, mounting the result widget as a new workspace tab.
    This establishes the Context → Workspace mount-source pattern, paralleling W-4
    (Assistant → Workspace, task 042). The Workspace pane resolves the receiving widget
    from `WorkspaceWidgetRegistry`. Use typed PaneEventBus channels (ADR-030 — no `any`)
    and `authenticatedFetch` for BFF calls (ADR-028). 042 and 043 are parallel-safe — they
    touch different code paths (Assistant pane vs Context wizard).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer expert in PaneEventBus (`@spaarke/ai-widgets`), Context-pane
    wizards (within SpaarkeAi), `WorkspaceWidgetRegistry`, React 19 + Fluent UI v9, and
    ADR-028 function-based auth. Bias toward establishing the pattern on ONE wizard
    cleanly — don't wire all Context wizards at once. The chosen wizard should be the most
    natural fit (Create Project recommended); if Create Project doesn't yet exist or isn't
    accessible, the operator picks an alternate at task start.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Operator-visible end-to-end demo on the dev environment: a user launches the chosen
    Context-pane wizard, completes its steps including the new "Add result to Workspace"
    final step, and on completion a result widget mounts as a new workspace tab via
    `widget_load` dispatch. Code changes meet ADR-021 (Fluent v9), ADR-022 (React 19),
    ADR-030 (typed channels — no `any`), ADR-028 (function-based auth). FR-03 acceptance
    criteria satisfied. Pattern established for future Context wizards (extensibility
    documented in &lt;notes&gt;).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per plan §4 Phase 4 and FR-03, the Context pane is the second of two not-yet-implemented
      mount sources for the Workspace pane (the other is Assistant, addressed by W-4 / task
      042). The Context pane hosts wizards that produce results (e.g., "Create Project",
      "Add Stakeholder", "Generate Summary"). Today, wizard results are typically displayed
      inline in the Context pane or saved to Dataverse. R4 adds the optional "Add result to
      Workspace" final step that promotes a wizard result into a workspace tab — same
      `widget_load` mechanism as W-4 but invoked from a different source pane.

      ONE wizard is wired in this task to establish the pattern. Plan recommends "Create
      Project" — it produces a result (the new project record) that's a natural fit for a
      DocumentViewer / RecordSummary-style widget tab. If Create Project isn't the right
      pick (doesn't exist; not in scope; operator prefers another), the operator picks an
      alternate at task start.

      The receiving wrapper is the same as W-4: `WorkspaceWidgetRegistry` (Direct widget
      wrapper per the two-wrapper model). The `widget_load` event type was defined / extended
      by task 042 — reuse it. If 042 hasn't shipped yet (043 only depends on 010, not on
      042 — they're parallel-safe), then this task may need to define the payload type
      itself. Coordinate via the parallel-group E execution wave.

      ADR-028 invariants: NO token snapshots; use `useAuth()` + `authenticatedFetch`.
      ADR-030 invariant: typed channels — no `any` payloads.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/ (Context pane wizard — exact path determined during Step 3)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/PaneEventBus.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/PaneEventBusContext.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/PaneEventTypes.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/useDispatchPaneEvent.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/registry/WorkspaceWidgetRegistry.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/registry/ContextWidgetRegistry.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/registry/register-context-widgets.ts</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 tokens only. NO hex, NO `rgba()`, NO Fluent v8.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 only for Code Pages. NO React 16 fallbacks.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-030">PaneEventBus channels MUST be typed — NO `any` payloads. Reuse the `widget_load` payload type defined in `PaneEventTypes.ts` (extended by 042 OR define here if 042 hasn't landed yet — coordinate via parallel-group E).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Function-based auth via `@spaarke/auth` `authenticatedFetch`. NO token snapshots in props/state.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Result widgets live in `@spaarke/ai-widgets` (or `@spaarke/*` lib family). Don't duplicate widget code inside the wizard.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">ONE wizard only. Wiring all Context wizards is OUT OF SCOPE — pattern-establishment, not coverage. Future wizards adopt the pattern in follow-up rounds.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">"Add result to Workspace" final step MUST be optional (don't force every wizard run to mount a tab). Surface as an explicit final-step user choice.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Operator confirms the chosen wizard at task start. Record in &lt;notes&gt;.</constraint>
  </constraints>

