  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Confirm dependencies">
      Verify task 010 (W-1 dashboard+widget model doc) is ✅ in TASK-INDEX.md. If not complete, STOP and surface the blocker per CLAUDE.md "Human Escalation Triggers". Note: 042 is NOT a hard dependency — 043 can run in parallel.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Operator confirms wizard choice">
      Surface the choice to operator: confirm recommended "Create Project" wizard OR substitute. Record the choice in &lt;notes&gt;. Without operator confirmation, do NOT proceed past Step 3.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Locate the chosen wizard">
      Inspect `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/` to find the Context-pane wizard component. Read its existing final-step / completion logic. Record its exact path in &lt;notes&gt; for future reference.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Load context">
      Read W-1 doc (010 output), ADR-030, ADR-028, PaneEventBus source files, ContextWidgetRegistry + WorkspaceWidgetRegistry source, Calendar widget Pattern D reference, and the chosen wizard's component.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Coordinate widget_load payload type">
      Check `PaneEventTypes.ts` for the `widget_load` payload type. If task 042 has landed it, REUSE the same shape. If not (043 executing before 042 in parallel-group E), DEFINE it here per ADR-030 (typed, no `any`). The type must accommodate both Assistant- and Context-initiated dispatches.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Add 'Add result to Workspace' final step">
      Modify the chosen wizard to add the optional final step. Use Fluent v9 components for the UI (checkbox or button labeled "Add result to Workspace"). On submit/finish, IF the option is selected, dispatch `widget_load` on the workspace channel with the typed payload (widget type ID + result data). If not selected, complete the wizard normally.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Select / verify receiving widget">
      Identify which widget renders the result (e.g., a project summary widget, a record viewer, etc.). If it already exists in `@spaarke/ai-widgets` and is registered via `registerWorkspaceWidget()`, reuse. If not, build a minimal viewer following Calendar Pattern D and register it. Use `useAuth()` + `authenticatedFetch` for any BFF call inside the widget.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify Workspace pane receives + mounts">
      Confirm the Workspace pane subscribes to the workspace channel and handles `widget_load` correctly (same mechanism as 042). If 042 has fixed the receiving path, this should be a no-op verification. If not, fix in place WITHOUT introducing new channel mechanics.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Build">
      Run `npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund` (if needed) and `npm run build` for SpaarkeAi + `@spaarke/ai-widgets`. Run `tsc --noEmit` on touched packages. 0 errors expected.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Unit tests">
      Add focused tests: (a) wizard's final-step dispatch correctly constructs the typed payload (mocked); (b) the option being unchecked does NOT dispatch; (c) the receiving widget resolves via the registry for the dispatched type ID.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Deploy">
      Deploy SpaarkeAi via `code-page-deploy` skill. Verify deployment to dev environment succeeds.
    </step>
    <step order="12" name="UI test">
      Per &lt;ui-tests&gt; below: execute end-to-end on dev environment; verify wizard completion mounts a workspace tab; verify dark-mode parity; verify the "Add result to Workspace" option is genuinely optional (unchecked = no tab mount).
    </step>
    <step order="13" name="Bundle-size check">
      Measure SpaarkeAi gzip bundle delta vs 918 KB R3 baseline (NFR-08). Record in &lt;notes&gt;. New widgets should lazy-load via registry factory.
    </step>
    <step order="14" name="Document pattern for future wizards">
      Add a brief note to `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/` (or a follow-up section in the W-1 / W-2 doc if appropriate) explaining how future Context wizards adopt the same "Add result to Workspace" pattern. Reference this task as the canonical example.
    </step>
    <step order="15" name="Update TASK-INDEX">
      Edit `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: flip task 043 from 🔲 → ✅ completed.
    </step>
    <step order="16" name="Document deviations + operator demo">
      Record the chosen wizard, any pivots, and bundle-size delta. Surface the live demo to the operator for FR-03 acceptance sign-off.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
