  <ui-tests>
    <test name="Context → Workspace end-to-end demo (FR-03 acceptance)">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?appid={app-id}&amp;pagetype=custom&amp;name=sprk_spaarkeai</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Open SpaarkeAi in the dev environment; verify Context pane is accessible</step>
        <step>Launch the chosen wizard (e.g., Create Project) from the Context pane</step>
        <step>Complete the wizard steps with valid inputs</step>
        <step>Reach the final step; check the "Add result to Workspace" option</step>
        <step>Submit / finish the wizard</step>
        <step>Observe the Workspace pane mount a new tab labeled with the result (e.g., the new project name)</step>
        <step>Verify the new tab is selectable and shows the result widget</step>
        <step>Verify the tab is closable per existing tab semantics</step>
        <step>Check browser console: 0 JavaScript errors</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>End-to-end demo works as described in FR-03 acceptance; tab mounts only when option is checked; no console errors.</expected>
    </test>

    <test name="'Add result to Workspace' option is optional">
      <steps>
        <step>Repeat the wizard run from the previous test</step>
        <step>On the final step, leave the "Add result to Workspace" option UNCHECKED</step>
        <step>Submit / finish the wizard</step>
        <step>Verify the wizard completes normally (result saved to Dataverse / inline display)</step>
        <step>Verify NO new tab is mounted in the Workspace pane</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Workspace mount is genuinely opt-in; default behavior (option unchecked) does NOT mount.</expected>
    </test>

    <test name="Dark Mode Compliance (ADR-021)">
      <steps>
        <step>Toggle dark mode in D365 settings</step>
        <step>Repeat the demo: launch wizard, check the option, finish</step>
        <step>Verify the wizard final-step UI renders cleanly in dark mode</step>
        <step>Verify the new workspace tab renders cleanly in dark mode</step>
        <step>Verify all colors use Fluent v9 semantic tokens</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Dark-mode renders cleanly; all colors via Fluent v9 semantic tokens per ADR-021.</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the operator launches the chosen Context wizard and completes it with "Add result to Workspace" checked, When the wizard finishes, Then a `widget_load` event is dispatched on the workspace channel with a typed payload identifying the result widget + data.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the option is left unchecked, When the wizard finishes, Then NO `widget_load` event is dispatched and the workspace pane is unchanged.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the workspace channel receives the `widget_load` event, When the Workspace pane handles it, Then the result widget resolves via `WorkspaceWidgetRegistry` and mounts as a new tab.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given ADR-030 requires typed channels, When the code is reviewed, Then no `any` payload types appear in the dispatch path; the `widget_load` payload type is shared with 042 (or defined here if 042 hasn't landed).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given ADR-028 requires function-based auth, When the receiving widget calls the BFF, Then it uses `authenticatedFetch`; NO token snapshots.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given ADR-021 requires Fluent v9 tokens, When the wizard final step and new tab render in light + dark mode, Then all colors use semantic tokens.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given task 043 is executing, When this task completes, Then TASK-INDEX.md shows task 043 as ✅ completed.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Operator MUST confirm the chosen Context wizard at task start. Recommended: "Create Project". Alternatives: "Add Stakeholder", "Generate Summary", or whichever Context wizard makes the most natural demo pairing for the operator's planned walkthrough. Record the choice here at task close.

    PARALLEL-GROUP E with task 042: both tasks depend on 010 (W-1) but NOT on each other. They touch different code paths — 042 modifies the Assistant pane (`ConversationPane.tsx`), 043 modifies a Context-pane wizard component. Both extend `PaneEventTypes.ts` for the `widget_load` payload — coordinate the type definition so it lands cleanly (whichever task ships first defines it; the other reuses).

    File-overlap risk: `PaneEventTypes.ts` is touched by BOTH 042 and 043. The auto-demotion rule in task-create Step 3.8 would normally force serialization, BUT here the overlap is a single tiny union/type addition that can be coordinated trivially. Decision: keep both parallel-safe; on first PR merge to either, the second rebases and reuses. Document this in the PR description.

    The Calendar widget Pattern D (R3 task 115) is the canonical reference for the receiving widget shape. Reuse a result-viewer widget if one already exists; build a minimal one if not. DO NOT inline widget code in the wizard.

    PATTERN ESTABLISHMENT not COVERAGE: only ONE wizard is wired. Future Context wizards adopt the pattern in follow-up rounds. The notes/context-workspace-mount-pattern.md output is the carrier of that guidance.

    AUTO-DEMOTION: this task does NOT touch `.claude/` paths, so the `.claude/` permission boundary does not apply.
  </notes>

